title: The Indian Army has recently inducted 100 robotic mules (Multi-Utility Legged Equipment)# Army
description:
The Indian Army has recently inducted 100 robotic dogs, also known as Multi-Utility Legged Equipment (MULES), into its arsenal. These robotic dogs are designed to operate in challenging terrains, such as high altitudes, deserts, and snow, and are equipped with advanced sensors and thermal imaging.  
They can perform a variety of tasks, including: 
Surveillance: 
They can provide real-time surveillance data through high-resolution cameras and sensors. 
Logistics support: 
They can carry light loads through steep and uneven terrain. 
Combat roles: 
They can be integrated with small arms for combat purposes. 
Anti-drone warfare: 
They can be armed with assault rifles equipped with infrared/thermal vision to detect and engage drones.
